volumetric_efficiency_modifier.name: Volumetric Efficiency Modifier
volumetric_efficiency_modifier.description: Multiplied with float_FFFF49D8 and added to Volumetric Efficiency on certain condition. (TODO: identify condition).

bcs_dc_multiplier_from_iat.name: BCS DC Multiplier From IAT
bcs_dc_multiplier_from_iat.description: Percentage applied to the boost control solenoid duty cycle as a function of the intake air temperature. 100% applies no change.

bcs_dc_adjust_baro_pressure.name: BCS DC Multiplier From Barometric Pressure
bcs_dc_adjust_baro_pressure.description: Percentage applied to the boost control solenoid duty cycle as a function of the barometric pressure. 100% applies no change.

bcs_dc_base.name: BCS DC Base
bcs_dc_base.description: Base boost control solenoid duty cycle as a function of throttle position and RPM. Multipliers are applied to this value. 100% is open, 0% is closed.

bcs_dc_correction_base.name: BCS DC Adjustment Base
bcs_dc_correction_base.description: Percentage added to the boost control solenoid duty cycle as a function of (absolute load - target absolute load). Incremental BCS DC Adjustment is added to this value.

bsc_dc_adjust_battery_voltage.name: BCS DC Adjustment From Battery Voltage
bsc_dc_adjust_battery_voltage.description: Percentage added to the boost control solenoid duty cycle as a function of battery voltage.

bcs_dc_adjust_load_target_normal.name: Incremental BCS DC Adjustment (Normal Conditions)
bcs_dc_adjust_load_target_normal.description: Percentage added to the boost control solenoid duty cycle as a function of (absolute load - target absolute load)

bcs_dc_adjust_boost_limit_exceeded.name: Incremental BCS DC Adjustment (Overboost)
bcs_dc_adjust_boost_limit_exceeded.description: Percentage added to the boost control solenoid duty cycle as a function of overboost amount.

bsc_dc_adjust_boost_targeting.name: Incremental BCS DC Adjustment (Boost Targeting)
bsc_dc_adjust_boost_targeting.description: Percentage added to the boost control solenoid duty cycle as a function of (current MAP - target MAP)

boost_limit_modifier.name: MAP Limit Modifier
boost_limit_modifier.description: Percentage applied to the MAP limit.

map_limit_threshold.name: MAP Limit Hysteresis (kPa)
map_limit_threshold.description: This number is subtracted from the boost limit to get the pressure the MAP must fall below to exit the overboost condition

base_target_load_overload.name: Base Target Load (Overload)

pids.description: The ratio of actual AFR to stoichiometry for a given mixture. lambda = 1.0 is at stoichiometry, rich mixtures labmda < 1.0, and lean mixtures lambda > 1.0.

pids.description: Timing advance in degrees of the camshafts

pids.description: Ambient air temperature

pids.description: External atmospheric pressure

pids.description: Voltage supplied to ECU

pids.description: The target fuel-air equivalence ratio

pids.description: The engine RPM the ECU is targetting

pids.description: The throttle position that the ECU is targetting

pids.description: The time each injector is held open it its injection cycle

pids.description: The high pressure fuel rail's pressure

pids.description: The temperature of air measured by the MAF sensor

pids.description: The degrees that the spark timing is retarded as response to the knock sensor

pids.description: The percentage difference from the base amount calculated from long term oxygen sensor measurements. Negative means fuel is reduced (too rich). Positive means fuel is added (too lean).

pids.name: Short term fuel trim (primary)

pids.name: Short term fuel trim (secondary)
pids.description: The short term fuel trim calculated from the secondary oxygen sensor

pids.description: The pressure of the intake manifold

pids.description: The flow rate of air measured by the MAF sensor

pids.description: The voltage output by the MAF sensor

pids.name: Relative throttle position
pids.description: The throttle position relative to the learned closed position

pids.name: Timing advance
pids.description: The spark timing advance relative to TDC

pids.name: Wastegate control solenoid duty cycle
pids.description: The duty cycle of the boost control solenoid.

pids.name: Fuel injection amount
pids.description: The amount of fuel injected in each cylinder per cycle

pids.name: Air to fuel ratio
pids.description: The air to fuel ratio measured by the wideband oxygen sensor

pids.name: FuelAir commanded ratio
pids.description: The air to fuel ratio targeted by the ECU

pids.name: Clutch pedal position
pids.description: Clutch pedal position. 0 is released, 1 is depressed.

pids.description: 0 - gearbox is in drive, 1 - gearbox is in neutral

pids.description: Voltage output by the MAP sensor

pids.description: Voltage output by the fuel sensor

pids.name: Target fuel rail pressure
pids.description: The fuel rail pressure the ECU is targetting

pids.name: Oxygen sensor voltage
pids.description: Voltage of the narrow band oxygen sensor
